actual: SELECT AVG(L.UA) AS Average_UA FROM Laboratory L JOIN Patient P ON L.ID=P.ID WHERE L.UA<6.0--Assuming normal uric acid level is less than 6.0 mg/dL AND L.Date=( SELECT MAX(Date) FROM Laboratory WHERE ID=P.ID ) GROUP BY P.ID;

question: Provide all ID, sex and birthday of patients whose urea nitrogen (UN) just within the borderline of passing?
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.Birthday, T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.UN = 29
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX, p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.UN BETWEEN<lower_borderline_value>AND<upper_borderline_value>;

question: Provide the ID, sex, birthday of all patients diagnosed with 'RA' that are within the UN normal index.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.UN < 30 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'RA'
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX, p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Diagnosis='RA' AND l.UN IS NOT NULL;

question: How many male patients are are with creatinine index out of the normal range?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CRE >= 1.5 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientsOutOfRange FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.SEX='Male' AND (l.CRE<0.6 OR l.CRE>1.2);

question: Are there more male patients with creatinine not within the normal range than female? True or False?
expected: SELECT CASE WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'M' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CRE >= 1.5
actual: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN p.SEX='Male' AND l.CRE NOT BETWEEN 0.6 AND 1.2 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Male_Count, SUM(CASE WHEN p.SEX='Female' AND l.CRE NOT BETWEEN 0.6 AND 1.2 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Female_Count FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID HAVING Male_Count>Female_Count;

question: What is the highest total bilirubin level recorded? List out the patient details with ID, sex and birthday with that index.
expected: SELECT T2.`T-BIL`, T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID ORDER BY T2.`T-BIL` DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX, p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.T-BIL=(SELECT MAX(T-BIL) FROM Laboratory);

question: List and group all patients by sex for total bilirubin (T-BIL) level not within the normal range.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' THEN T1.ID END , CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'M' THEN T1.ID END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` >= 2.0
actual: SELECT p.SEX, COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l."T-BIL"<1.2 OR l."T-BIL">1.9--Assuming normal range for T-BIL is 1.2 to 1.9 mg/dL GROUP BY p.SEX;

question: Who is the oldest patient with the highest total cholesterol (T-CHO). State the patient ID and T-CHO index.
expected: SELECT T1.ID, T2.`T-CHO` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID ORDER BY T2.`T-CHO` DESC, T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.ID, l."T-CHO" FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.Birthday=(SELECT MIN(Birthday) FROM Patient WHERE ID IN (SELECT ID FROM Laboratory ORDER BY "T-CHO" DESC LIMIT 1)) ORDER BY l."T-CHO" DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the average age of the male patient with high cholesterol?
expected: SELECT AVG(STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday)) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`T-CHO` >= 250 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT AVG(JULIANDAY('now')-JULIANDAY(Birthday))/365.25 AS average_age FROM Patient WHERE SEX='Male' AND ID IN ( SELECT ID FROM Laboratory WHERE T-CHO>240 );

question: Provide list of patients and their diagnosis with triglyceride (TG) index greater than 100 of the normal range?
expected: SELECT T1.ID, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG > 300
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.Diagnosis, l.TG FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.TG>100;

question: For all patients with triglyceride (TG) level beyond the normal range, how many are age more than 50 years?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG > 200 AND STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 50
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.TG>150 AND (julianday('now')-julianday(p.Birthday))/365.25>50;

question: List all outpatient within normal range of creatinine phosphokinase. Give me the distinct ids.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CPK < 250 AND T1.Admission = '-'
actual: SELECT DISTINCT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.CPK BETWEEN 0 AND 200;--Assuming normal range for CPK is 0 to 200

question: For patient born between 1936-1956, how many male patients have creatinine phosphokinase beyond the normal range?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) BETWEEN '1936' AND '1956' AND T1.SEX = 'M' AND T2.CPK >= 250
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientsWithHighCPK FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.SEX='Male' AND p.Birthday BETWEEN '1936-01-01' AND '1956-12-31' AND l.CPK>(SELECT MAX(CPK) FROM Laboratory)*1.2;--Assuming normal range is defined as 1.2 times the maximum value

question: Provide ID, sex and age of patient who has blood glucose (GLU) not within normal range but with total cholesterol(T-CHO) within normal range.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX , STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GLU >= 180 AND T2.`T-CHO` < 250
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX, (strftime('%Y', 'now')-strftime('%Y', p.Birthday)) AS Age FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.GLU NOT BETWEEN 70 AND 100 AND l.T_CHO BETWEEN 125 AND 200;

question: List each patient's ID and blood glucose (GLU) index that were within normal range for patient's whose data was first recorded in 1991.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T2.GLU FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.`First Date`) = '1991' AND T2.GLU < 180
actual: SELECT p.ID, l.GLU FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p."First Date">='1991-01-01' AND l.GLU BETWEEN 70 AND 140;

question: List the patient ID, sex and birthday who has abnormal white blood cell count. Group them by sex and list the patient by age in ascending order.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.WBC <= 3.5 OR T2.WBC >= 9.0 ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC
actual: SELECT P.ID AS patient_id, P.SEX, P.Birthday FROM Patient P JOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID=L.ID WHERE L.WBC<4 OR L.WBC>10--Assuming abnormal WBC count is less than 4 or greater than 10 GROUP BY P.SEX, P.ID, P.Birthday ORDER BY P.SEX, DATE('now')-P.Birthday;--Ordering by age in ascending order

question: What are the patient's diagnosis for those who has lower red blood blood cell? State their ID and age.
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis, T1.ID , STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) -STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RBC < 3.5
actual: SELECT P.ID, (strftime('%Y', 'now')-strftime('%Y', P.Birthday)) AS Age, E.Diagnosis FROM Patient P JOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID=L.ID JOIN Examination E ON P.ID=E.ID WHERE L.RBC<(SELECT AVG(RBC) FROM Laboratory);

question: For all the female patient age 50 and above, who has abnormal red blood cell count. State if they were admitted to hospital.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.Admission FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND (T2.RBC <= 3.5 OR T2.RBC >= 6.0) AND STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) >= 50
actual: SELECT P.ID, P.SEX, P.Birthday, L.RBC, P.Admission FROM Patient P JOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID=L.ID WHERE P.SEX='Female' AND (strftime('%Y', 'now')-strftime('%Y', P.Birthday))>=50 AND L.RBC<4.0;--Assuming abnormal RBC count is less than 4.0 million cells/mcL

question: Among all outpatients, list out those have low hemoglobin level. State the different IDs and their sex.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.HGB < 10 AND T1.Admission = '-'
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.HGB<13.0;--Assuming 13.0 is the threshold for low hemoglobin level for outpatients

question: Among the patients who were diagnosed with SLE, who is the oldest with normal hemoglobin level. Provide the ID and sex.
expected: SELECT T1.ID, T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE' AND T2.HGB > 10 AND T2.HGB < 17 ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.Diagnosis='SLE' AND l.HGB>=13--Assuming normal hemoglobin level is 13 or higher ORDER BY p.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1;

question: Name the ID and age of patient with two or more laboratory examinations which show their hematoclit level exceeded the normal range.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID IN ( SELECT ID FROM Laboratory WHERE HCT > 52 GROUP BY ID HAVING COUNT(ID) >= 2 )
actual: SELECT p.ID, (strftime('%Y', 'now')-strftime('%Y', p.Birthday)) AS Age FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.HCT>0.45--Assuming 0.45 is the upper limit for normal HCT levels GROUP BY p.ID HAVING COUNT(l.ID)>=2;

question: From laboratory examinations in 1991, what is the average hematoclit level that is lower than the normal range.
expected: SELECT AVG(T2.HCT) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.HCT < 29 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1991'
actual: SELECT AVG(HCT) AS average_hct FROM Laboratory WHERE HCT<40 AND Date BETWEEN '1991-01-01' AND '1991-12-31';

question: For patients with abnormal platelet level, state the number of patients with lower than normal range. How is it compare to the number of patients with higher than normal range?
expected: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID
actual: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN L.PLT<150 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Lower_Than_Normal, SUM(CASE WHEN L.PLT>450 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Higher_Than_Normal FROM Laboratory L JOIN Patient P ON L.ID=P.ID WHERE L.PLT<150 OR L.PLT>450;

question: For laboratory examinations take in 1984, list all patients below 50 years old with normal platelet level.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PLT > 100 AND T2.PLT < 400 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) < '50' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1984'
actual: SELECT p.ID, p.SEX, p.Birthday, l.Date, l.PLT FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.Date BETWEEN '1984-01-01' AND '1984-12-31' AND (strftime('%Y', 'now')-strftime('%Y', p.Birthday))<50 AND l.PLT BETWEEN 150000 AND 450000;

question: For all patients who are older than 55 years old, what is the percentage of female who has abnormal prothrombin time (PT)?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PT >= 14 AND T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 55
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN p.SEX='Female' AND l.PT>1.5 THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS female_abnormal_pt_percentage FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE (julianday('now')-julianday(p.Birthday))/365.25>55;

question: List all patients who first came to the hospital after year 1992 with prothrombin time (PT) level that are normal. Sort the ID by the date of laboratory examiniation.
expected: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.`First Date`) = '1992' AND T2.PT < 14 ORDER BY T1.ID
actual: SELECT p.ID, l.Date FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p."First Date">'1992-12-31' AND l.PT IS NOT NULL AND l.PT BETWEEN 10 AND 13 ORDER BY l.Date;

question: For the examinations done after 1997/1/1, how many of them have the result of an inactivated partial prothrom bin time?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Date > '1997-01-01' AND T2.APTT >= 45
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS ExaminationCount FROM Examination WHERE "Examination Date">'1997-01-01' AND KCT='inactivated partial prothrombin time';

question: For the patients with an abnormal activated partial prothrom bin time, how many of them have a mild thrombosis?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T3.Thrombosis = 3 AND T2.APTT < 45
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MildThrombosisCount FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID WHERE e.APTT>normal_value--Replace normal_value with the actual threshold for abnormal APTT AND e.Thrombosis=1;--Assuming 1 indicates mild thrombosis

question: Among the male patients who have a normal level of white blood cells, how many of them have an abnormal fibrinogen level?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.FG <= 150 OR T2.FG >= 450 AND T2.WBC > 3.5 AND T2.WBC < 9.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS abnormal_fibrinogen_count FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.SEX='Male' AND l.WBC BETWEEN 4000 AND 10000--Assuming normal WBC range AND l.FG NOT BETWEEN 200 AND 400;--Assuming abnormal fibrinogen level range

question: How many patients born after 1980/1/1 have an abnormal fibrinogen level?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.FG <= 150 OR T2.FG >= 450 AND T1.Birthday > '1980-01-01'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.Birthday>'1980-01-01' AND l.FG IS NOT NULL AND l.FG<150;--Assuming abnormal fibrinogen level is defined as less than 150 mg/dL

question: Please list the disease names of the patients that have a proteinuria level higher than normal.
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`U-PRO` >= 30
actual: SELECT DISTINCT p.Diagnosis FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.U-PRO='high';

question: Which patient has a normal proteinuria level and is diagnosed with SLE? Please give his or her patient ID.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`U-PRO` > 0 AND T2.`U-PRO` < 30 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE'
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Diagnosis='SLE' AND l.U-PRO='Normal';

question: How many patients with an Ig G lower than normal has the symptom of abortion?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG < 900 AND T3.Symptoms = 'abortion'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE e."aCL IgG"<(SELECT AVG("aCL IgG") FROM Examination) AND e.Symptoms LIKE '%abortion%';

question: Among the patients with a normal Ig G level, how many of them have symptoms?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG BETWEEN 900 AND 2000 AND T3.Symptoms IS NOT NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientWithSymptoms FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID WHERE e."aCL IgG" IS NOT NULL AND e."aCL IgG" BETWEEN 7 AND 13--Assuming normal range for IgG AND e."Symptoms" IS NOT NULL AND e."Symptoms"<>'';

question: For the patient who has the highest Ig A within the normal range, what is his or her diagnosis?
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGA BETWEEN 80 AND 500 ORDER BY T2.IGA DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT e.Diagnosis FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID WHERE e."aCL IgA"=( SELECT MAX(e2."aCL IgA") FROM Examination e2 WHERE e2."aCL IgA"<=<normal_range_value>)

question: How many patients with a normal Ig A level came to the hospital after 1990/1/1?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGA BETWEEN 80 AND 500 AND T1.`First Date` > '1990-01-01'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.IGA='normal' AND p.First_Date>'1990-01-01';

question: For the patients with an abnormal Ig M level, what is the most common disease they are diagnosed with?
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGM NOT BETWEEN 40 AND 400 GROUP BY T1.Diagnosis ORDER BY COUNT(T1.Diagnosis) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT Diagnosis, COUNT(*) AS DiagnosisCount FROM Examination WHERE aCL IgM>normal_value--Replace normal_value with the actual threshold for abnormal IgM levels GROUP BY Diagnosis ORDER BY DiagnosisCount DESC LIMIT 1;

question: How many patients with a normal C-reactive protein don't have their data recorded?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.CRP = '-' OR T2.CRP = '+-' OR T2.CRP < 1.0) AND T1.Description IS NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientsWithoutData FROM Patient p WHERE NOT EXISTS ( SELECT 1 FROM Laboratory l WHERE l.ID=p.ID AND l.CRP='Normal' );

question: Among the patients whose C-reactive protein level is abnormal, how many of them aren't 18 yet?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.CRP != '-' OR T2.CRP != '+-') AND T2.CRP >= 1.0 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) < '18'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Under_18_Count FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.CRP='abnormal' AND (julianday('now')-julianday(p.Birthday))/365<18;

question: How many patients with a normal Rhuematoid Factor has a positive measure of degree of coagulation?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.RA = '-' OR '+-') AND T3.KCT = '+'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l.RF='Normal' AND l.FG>0;

question: Please list the diseases of the patients born after 1995-1-1 and have a normal Rhuematoid Factor.
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.RA = '-' OR '+-') AND T1.Birthday > 1995-01-01
actual: SELECT DISTINCT e.Diagnosis FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.Birthday>'1995-01-01' AND l.RF='Normal';

question: Please list the ID of the patient whose RF is normal and who is older than 60.
expected: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RF < 20 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 60
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.RF='normal' AND (julianday('now')-julianday(p.Birthday))/365>60;

question: How many patients with a normal RF don't have thrombosis?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RF < 20 AND T1.Thrombosis = 0
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID WHERE e.RF='normal' AND e.Thrombosis=0;

question: How many patients with a normal level of complement 3 have a P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.C3 > 35 AND T1.`ANA Pattern` = 'P'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l.C3='normal' AND e."ANA Pattern"='P';

question: Among the patients whose level of complement 3 isn't normal, which patient has the highest anti-Cardiolipin antibody concentration? Please list his or her ID.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.C3 <= 35 ORDER BY T2.IGA DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT e.ID FROM Examination e JOIN Laboratory l ON e.ID=l.ID WHERE l.C3<>'normal' ORDER BY e.aCL IgG DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Among the patients have blood clots in veins, how many of them have a normal level of complement 4?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.C4 > 10 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'APS'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_C4_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Thrombosis=1 AND l.C4=0;

question: How many patients have a normal level of anti-ribonuclear protein and have been admitted to the hospital?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RNP = 'negative' OR T2.RNP = '0' AND T1.Admission = '+'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS Normal_RNP_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.RNP='Normal' AND p.Admission IS NOT NULL;

question: Which is the youngest patient with an abnormal anti-ribonuclear protein level? Please list his or her date of birth.
expected: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RNP != '-' OR '+-' ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.RNP='abnormal' ORDER BY p.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Among the patients with normal anti-SM, how many of them have the most severe degree of thrombosis?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SM = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.Thrombosis = 1
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS SevereThrombosisCount FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID WHERE e.aCL IgG IS NULL AND e.Thrombosis=(SELECT MAX(Thrombosis) FROM Examination WHERE aCL IgG IS NULL);

question: For the patients with an abnormal anti-SM, please list the IDs of the three youngest ones.
expected: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SM != '-' OR T2.SM != '+-' ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 3
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.SM='abnormal' ORDER BY p.Birthday DESC LIMIT 3;

question: Please list the IDs of the patients who had the examination done after 1997/1/1 and had a normal anti-scl70.
expected: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SC170 = 'negative' AND T2.Date > 1997-01-01
actual: SELECT DISTINCT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e."Examination Date">'1997-01-01' AND l."SC170"='Normal';

question: Among the patients who has a normal anti-scl70, how many of them are male and have the symptom of vertigo?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SC170 = '-' OR T2.SC170 = '+-' AND T1.SEX = 'M' AND T3.Symptoms = 'vertigo'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientsWithVertigo FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE e."ANA"=0--Assuming normal anti-scl70 is represented by ANA=0 AND p.SEX='Male' AND e.Symptoms LIKE '%vertigo%';

question: How many patients with a normal anti-SSA came to the hospital before 1990?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSA = 'negative' OR '0' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) < '1990'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_Anti_SSA_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.SSA='Normal' AND l.Date<'1990-01-01';

question: Which patient is the first patient with an abnormal anti-SSA to come to the hospital? Please give his or her ID.
expected: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSA != 'negative' OR T2.SSA != '0' ORDER BY T1.`First Date` ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.SSA='abnormal' ORDER BY p."First Date" LIMIT 1;

question: How many patients have a normal anti-SSB and are diagnosed with SLE in the examination?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSB = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_SLE_Patients FROM Examination e JOIN Patient p ON e.ID=p.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Diagnosis='SLE' AND l.SSB='normal';

question: For the patients whose anti-SSB are normal, how many of them have other symptoms observed in their examination?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSB = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.Symptoms IS NOT NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.SSB='normal' AND e.Symptoms IS NOT NULL;

question: Among the patients who has a normal level of anti-centromere and a normal level of anti-SSB, how many of them are male?
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CENTROMEA = 'negative' OR '0' AND T2.SSB = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.CENTROMEA='normal' AND l.SSB='normal' AND p.SEX='male';

question: For the patients who have an abnormal level of anti-DNA, please list the diseases they are diagnosed with.
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.DNA >= 8 GROUP BY T1.ID, T1.Diagnosis
actual: SELECT DISTINCT p.Diagnosis FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.DNA='abnormal';

question: How many patients have a normal anti-DNA level, yet their data are not recorded.
expected: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.DNA < 8 AND T1.Description IS NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_Anti_DNA_Patients FROM Patient p LEFT JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.DNA='Normal' AND l.ID IS NULL;

question: Of the patients with an abnormal level of anti-DNA-II, how many of them admitted to the hospital?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`DNA-II` >= 8 AND T1.Admission = '+'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS Abnormal_Anti_DNA_II_Admitted FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l."DNA-II">0 AND p.Admission IS NOT NULL;

question: What is the percentage of patient who has a normal anti-DNA-II level, yet he or she is diagnosed with SLE?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`DNA-II` < 8 AND T1.Diagnosis LIKE '%SLE%'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN L."DNA-II"=0 AND P."Diagnosis"='SLE' THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS percentage FROM "Patient" P JOIN "Examination" E ON P."ID"=E."ID" JOIN "Laboratory" L ON P."ID"=L."ID" WHERE L."DNA-II"=0 OR P."Diagnosis"='SLE';

question: How many male patients have their glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase in the normal range?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT < 60 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientsWithNormalGOT FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.SEX='Male' AND l.GOT BETWEEN 0 AND 40;--Assuming normal range for GOT is 0-40 U/L

question: Among the patients who have an abnormal level of glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase, when was the youngest of them born?
expected: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT >= 60 ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT MIN(P.Birthday) AS Youngest_Birthday FROM Patient P JOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID=L.ID WHERE L.GOT>normal_value--Replace normal_value with the threshold for abnormal GOT levels

question: Please list the top three patients' birthdays with the highest glutamic pylvic transaminase in the normal range.
expected: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GPT < 60 ORDER BY T2.GPT DESC LIMIT 3
actual: SELECT p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.GPT BETWEEN 0 AND 40--Assuming normal range for GPT is 0-40 ORDER BY l.GPT DESC LIMIT 3;

question: For the patients with the normal glutamic pylvic transaminase level, how many of them are male?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT < 60 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatients FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.GPT IS NOT NULL AND l.GPT<=40 AND p.SEX='Male';

question: For the patient with the highest lactate dehydrogenase in the normal range, when was his or her data first recorded?
expected: SELECT T1.`First Date` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH < 500 ORDER BY T2.LDH DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT MIN(L.Date) AS First_Recorded_Date FROM Laboratory L JOIN Patient P ON L.ID=P.ID WHERE L.LDH IS NOT NULL AND L.LDH<=250--Assuming 250 is the upper limit of normal range for LDH AND L.LDH=(SELECT MAX(LDH) FROM Laboratory WHERE LDH IS NOT NULL AND LDH<=250);

question: When is the latest patient's medical data recorded? This patient should have an abnormal level of lactate dehydrogenase.
expected: SELECT T1.`First Date` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH >= 500 ORDER BY T1.`First Date` DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT MAX(L.Date) AS Latest_Medical_Data FROM Laboratory L JOIN Patient P ON L.ID=P.ID WHERE L.LDH>normal_value--Replace 'normal_value' with the actual threshold for abnormal LDH levels

question: For the patient with an abnormal alkaliphophatase level, how many of them are admitted to the hospital?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP >= 300 AND T1.Admission = '+'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS Abnormal_ALP_Patient_Count FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.ALP>120 AND p.Admission IS NOT NULL;

question: Among the patients followed at the outpatient clinic, how many of them have a normal level of alkaliphophatase?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP < 300 AND T1.Admission = '-'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS Normal_Alkaliphophatase_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.ALP BETWEEN 30 AND 120;--Assuming normal ALP range is between 30 and 120 U/L

question: Please list the diagnosis of the patients whose total protein is lower than normal.
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TP < 6.0
actual: SELECT DISTINCT e.Diagnosis FROM Examination e JOIN Laboratory l ON e.ID=l.ID WHERE l.TP<(SELECT AVG(TP) FROM Laboratory);

question: For the patients who are diagnosed with SJS, how many of them have a normal level of total protein?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SJS' AND T2.TP > 6.0 AND T2.TP < 8.5
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_Protein_Count FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Diagnosis='SJS' AND l.TP BETWEEN 6.0 AND 8.0;--Assuming normal total protein level is between 6.0 and 8.0 g/dL

question: What is the examination date of the patient whose albumin is the highest in the normal range?
expected: SELECT Date FROM Laboratory WHERE ALB BETWEEN 3.5 AND 5.5 ORDER BY ALB DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT e."Examination Date" FROM "Examination" e JOIN "Laboratory" l ON e.ID=l.ID WHERE l.ALB=(SELECT MAX(ALB) FROM "Laboratory" WHERE ALB<=5.0)--Assuming 5.0 is the upper limit of normal range for albumin

question: How many male patients have a normal level of both albumin and total protein?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'M' AND T2.ALB BETWEEN 3.5 AND 5.5 AND T2.TP BETWEEN 6.0 AND 8.5
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS MalePatientsWithNormalLevels FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.SEX='Male' AND l.ALB BETWEEN 3.5 AND 5.0 AND l.TP BETWEEN 6.0 AND 8.0;

question: What is the anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration of the female patient with the highest uric acid level in the normal range?
expected: SELECT T3.`aCL IgG`, T3.`aCL IgM`, T3.`aCL IgA` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.UA > 6.5 ORDER BY T2.UA DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT e."aCL IgG" FROM "Examination" e JOIN "Patient" p ON e."ID"=p."ID" JOIN "Laboratory" l ON p."ID"=l."ID" WHERE p."SEX"='Female' AND l."UA" BETWEEN 0 AND 7 ORDER BY l."UA" DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the highest anti-nucleus antibody concentration level of a patient with a normal creatinine level?
expected: SELECT T2.ANA FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T3.CRE < 1.5 ORDER BY T2.ANA DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT MAX(e.aCL IgG) AS highest_aCL_IgG FROM Examination e JOIN Laboratory l ON e.ID=l.ID WHERE l.CRE BETWEEN 0 AND 1;--Assuming normal creatinine level is between 0 and 1

question: Please list the patient's ID whose creatinine level is normal and whose anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration level is the highest.
expected: SELECT T2.ID FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.CRE < 1.5 ORDER BY `aCL IgA` DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l.CRE BETWEEN 0.6 AND 1.2 ORDER BY e.aCL IgG DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Among the patients whose total bilirubin is over the normal range, how many of them have a peripheral pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` >= 2 AND T3.`ANA Pattern` LIKE '%P%'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l."T-BIL">(SELECT MAX(value) FROM normal_ranges WHERE test='Total Bilirubin') AND e."ANA Pattern"='Peripheral';

question: What is the anti-nucleus antibody concentration of the patient whose total bilirubin is the highest in the normal range?
expected: SELECT T3.ANA FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` < 2.0 ORDER BY T2.`T-BIL` DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT e."aCL IgG", e."aCL IgM" FROM "Examination" e JOIN "Patient" p ON e."ID"=p."ID" JOIN "Laboratory" l ON p."ID"=l."ID" WHERE l."T-BIL"=( SELECT MAX("T-BIL") FROM "Laboratory" WHERE "T-BIL"<=1.2--Assuming 1.2 is the upper limit of the normal range for total bilirubin )

question: For the patients whose total cholesterol is higher than normal, how many of them have a negative measure of degree of coagulation?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-CHO` >= 250 AND T3.KCT = '-'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Negative_Coagulation_Count FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.T-CHO>200 AND l.APTT<30;

question: Among the patients whose total cholesterol is within the normal range, how many of them have a P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T3.`ANA Pattern` = 'P' AND T2.`T-CHO` < 250
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l."T-CHO" BETWEEN 125 AND 200 AND e."ANA Pattern" LIKE '%P%';

question: Among the patients with the normal level of triglyceride, how many of them have other symptoms observed?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG < 200 AND T1.Symptoms IS NOT NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Patients_With_Other_Symptoms FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l.TG BETWEEN 150 AND 199 AND e.Symptoms IS NOT NULL;

question: What is the disease name of the patient who has the highest level of triglyceride within the normal range?
expected: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG < 200 ORDER BY T2.TG DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.Diagnosis FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.TG<=150 ORDER BY l.TG DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Please list the IDs of the patients with no thrombosis and an abnormal level of creatinine phosphokinase.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Thrombosis > 0 AND T1.CPK < 250
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Thrombosis=0 AND l.CPK>normal_value;--Replace normal_value with the threshold for abnormal CPK levels

question: For the patients with a normal range of creatinine phosphokinase, how many of them have a positive measure of degree of coagulation?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.CPK < 250 AND (T3.KCT = '+' OR T3.RVVT = '+' OR T3.LAC = '+')
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PositiveCoagulationCount FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.CPK BETWEEN 0 AND 200--Assuming normal range for CPK is 0 to 200 AND l.FG>0;--Assuming positive measure of degree of coagulation is indicated by FG>0

question: When is the birthday of the oldest patient whose blood glucose is abnormal?
expected: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GLU > 180 ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT p.Birthday FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.GLU>140--Assuming abnormal blood glucose is defined as greater than 140 ORDER BY p.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1;

question: Among the patients with a normal blood glucose, how many of them don't have thrombosis?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.GLU < 180 AND T3.Thrombosis = 0
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS PatientsWithoutThrombosis FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE e.Thrombosis=0 AND e.GLU BETWEEN 70 AND 99;

question: How many patients accepted to the hospital have a normal level of white blood cells?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.WBC BETWEEN 3.5 AND 9 AND T1.Admission = '+'
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_WBC_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.WBC BETWEEN 4.0 AND 11.0;

question: How many patients diagnosed with SLE have a normal white blood cell level?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE' AND T2.WBC BETWEEN 3.5 AND 9
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Normal_WBC_Patients FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE p.Diagnosis='SLE' AND l.WBC BETWEEN 4.0 AND 11.0;

question: Please list the patient's ID if he or she has an abnormal level of red blood cell and is followed at the outpatient clinic.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RBC <= 3.5 OR T2.RBC >= 6 AND T1.Admission = '-'
actual: SELECT p.ID FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE l.RBC<4.0 OR l.RBC>6.0--Assuming abnormal levels are outside the range of 4.0 to 6.0 million cells per microliter AND p.Admission='Outpatient Clinic';

question: Among the patients who have a normal platelet level, how many of them have other symptoms observed?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PLT BETWEEN 100 AND 400 AND T1.Diagnosis IS NOT NULL
actual: SELECT COUNT(*) AS Patients_With_Symptoms FROM Patient p JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID WHERE l.PLT BETWEEN 150 AND 450 AND e.Symptoms IS NOT NULL;

question: Please list a patient's platelet level if it is within the normal range and if he or she is diagnosed with MCTD.
expected: SELECT T2.PLT FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'MCTD' AND T2.PLT BETWEEN 100 AND 400
actual: SELECT L.PLT FROM Laboratory L JOIN Patient P ON L.ID=P.ID WHERE L.PLT BETWEEN 150 AND 450 AND P.Diagnosis='MCTD';

question: For the male patients that have a normal prothrombin time, what is their average prothrombin time?
expected: SELECT AVG(T2.PT) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PT < 14 AND T1.SEX = 'M'
actual: SELECT AVG(Lab."PT") AS Average_Prothrombin_Time FROM "Patient" AS Pat JOIN "Laboratory" AS Lab ON Pat."ID"=Lab."ID" WHERE Pat."SEX"='Male' AND Lab."PT" IS NOT NULL AND Lab."PT" BETWEEN 11 AND 13.5;

question: How many patients with severe thrombosis have a normal prothrombin time?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.PT < 14 AND T3.Thrombosis < 3 AND T3.Thrombosis > 0
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.ID) AS PatientCount FROM Patient p JOIN Examination e ON p.ID=e.ID JOIN Laboratory l ON p.ID=l.ID WHERE e.Thrombosis=1 AND l.PT BETWEEN 11 AND 13.5;

question: How many gas stations in CZE has Premium gas?
expected: SELECT COUNT(GasStationID) FROM gasstations WHERE Country = 'CZE' AND Segment = 'Premium'
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT gs.GasStationID) AS PremiumGasStationsCount FROM gasstations gs JOIN transactions_1k t ON gs.GasStationID=t.GasStationID JOIN products p ON t.ProductID=p.ProductID WHERE gs.Country='CZE' AND p.Description='Premium';

question: What is the ratio of costumers who pay in EUR against customers who pay in CZK?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(Currency = 'EUR', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) / SUM(IIF(Currency = 'CZK', 1, 0)) FROM customers
actual: SELECT (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) FROM customers WHERE Currency='EUR')*1.0/(SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) FROM customers WHERE Currency='CZK') AS EUR_to_CZK_Ratio

question: In 2012, who had the least consumption in LAM?
expected: SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.date BETWEEN 201201 AND 201212 GROUP BY T1.CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date BETWEEN 20120101 AND 20121231 AND c.Segment='LAM' GROUP BY c.CustomerID ORDER BY TotalConsumption ASC LIMIT 1;

question: What was the average monthly consumption of customers in SME for the year 2013?
expected: SELECT AVG(T2.Consumption) / 12 FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND T1.Segment = 'SME'
actual: SELECT AVG(Consumption) AS AverageMonthlyConsumption FROM yearmonth ym JOIN customers c ON ym.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment='SME' AND strftime('%Y', ym.Date)='2013' GROUP BY strftime('%m', ym.Date);

question: Which customers, paying in CZK, consumed the most gas in 2011?
expected: SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Currency = 'CZK' GROUP BY T1.CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='CZK' AND ym.Date BETWEEN 201101 AND 201112 GROUP BY c.CustomerID ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC;

question: How many customers in KAM had a consumption of less than 30,000 for the year 2012?
expected: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT T2.CustomerID FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY T2.CustomerID HAVING SUM(T2.Consumption) < 30000 ) AS t1
actual: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment='KAM' AND ym.Date BETWEEN 20120101 AND 20121231 AND ym.Consumption<30000;

question: What was the difference in gas consumption between CZK-paying customers and EUR-paying customers in 2012?
expected: SELECT SUM(IIF(T1.Currency = 'CZK', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Currency = 'EUR', T2.Consumption, 0)) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2012'
actual: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency='CZK' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS CZK_Consumption, SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency='EUR' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS EUR_Consumption, SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency='CZK' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END)-SUM(CASE WHEN c.Currency='EUR' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_Difference FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date>=20120101 AND ym.Date<20130101;

question: Which year recorded the most gas use paid in EUR?
expected: SELECT SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Currency = 'EUR' GROUP BY SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT strftime('%Y', t.Date) AS Year, SUM(t.Amount*t.Price) AS TotalGasUse FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='EUR' GROUP BY Year ORDER BY TotalGasUse DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Which segment had the least consumption?
expected: SELECT T1.Segment FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID GROUP BY T1.Segment ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT Segment, SUM(Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID=customers.CustomerID GROUP BY Segment ORDER BY TotalConsumption ASC LIMIT 1;

question: Which year recorded the most consumption of gas paid in CZK?
expected: SELECT SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Currency = 'CZK' GROUP BY SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT strftime('%Y', t.Date) AS Year, SUM(t.Amount*t.Price) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='CZK' GROUP BY Year ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What was the gas consumption peak month for SME customers in 2013?
expected: SELECT SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 5, 2) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND T1.Segment = 'SME' GROUP BY SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 5, 2) ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT strftime('%Y-%m', y.Date) AS Month, SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth y JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment='SME' AND strftime('%Y', y.Date)='2013' GROUP BY Month ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the difference in the annual average consumption of the customers with the least amount of consumption paid in CZK for 2013 between SME and LAM, LAM and KAM, and KAM and SME?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Currency = 'CZK' AND T2.Consumption = ( SELECT MIN(Consumption) FROM yearmonth ) AND T2.Date >= 201301
actual: WITH AnnualConsumption AS ( SELECT c.Segment, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE ym.Date BETWEEN 20130101 AND 20131231 AND c.Currency='CZK' GROUP BY c.CustomerID, c.Segment ), AverageConsumption AS ( SELECT Segment, AVG(TotalConsumption) AS AvgConsumption FROM AnnualConsumption GROUP BY Segment ), ConsumptionDifferences AS ( SELECT 'SME vs LAM' AS Comparison, (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='SME')-(SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='LAM') AS Difference UNION ALL SELECT 'LAM vs KAM', (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='LAM')-(SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='KAM') UNION ALL SELECT 'KAM vs SME', (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='KAM')-(SELECT AvgConsumption FROM AverageConsumption WHERE Segment='SME') ) SELECT*FROM ConsumptionDifferences;

question: Which of the three segmentsSME, LAM and KAMhas the biggest and lowest percentage increases in consumption paid in EUR between 2012 and 2013?
expected: SELECT CAST((SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0))) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)), CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
actual: WITH ConsumptionBySegment AS ( SELECT c.Segment, SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', t.Date)='2012' THEN t.Amount*t.Price END) AS Consumption2012, SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', t.Date)='2013' THEN t.Amount*t.Price END) AS Consumption2013 FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY c.Segment ), PercentageIncrease AS ( SELECT Segment, ((Consumption2013-Consumption2012)/Consumption2012)*100 AS PercentageIncrease FROM ConsumptionBySegment WHERE Consumption2012>0 ) SELECT Segment, PercentageIncrease FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY PercentageIncrease DESC LIMIT 1; SELECT Segment, PercentageIncrease FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY PercentageIncrease ASC LIMIT 1;

question: How much did customer 6 consume in total between August and November 2013?
expected: SELECT SUM(Consumption) FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID = 6 AND Date BETWEEN '201308' AND '201311'
actual: SELECT SUM(Amount) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k WHERE CustomerID=6 AND Date BETWEEN '2013-08-01' AND '2013-11-30';

question: How many more "discount" gas stations does the Czech Republic have compared to Slovakia?
expected: SELECT SUM(IIF(Country = 'CZE', 1, 0)) - SUM(IIF(Country = 'SVK', 1, 0)) FROM gasstations WHERE Segment = 'Discount'
actual: SELECT (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM gasstations WHERE Country='Czech Republic' AND Segment='discount')-(SELECT COUNT(*) FROM gasstations WHERE Country='Slovakia' AND Segment='discount') AS Difference

question: How much more was customer 7 consuming in April 2013 than customer 5?
expected: SELECT SUM(IIF(CustomerID = 7, Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(CustomerID = 5, Consumption, 0)) FROM yearmonth WHERE Date = '201304'
actual: SELECT (SELECT Consumption FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID=7 AND Date=201304)-(SELECT Consumption FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID=5 AND Date=201304) AS ConsumptionDifference

question: Is it true that more SMEs pay in Czech koruna than in euros? If so, how many more?
expected: SELECT SUM(Currency = 'CZK') - SUM(Currency = 'EUR') FROM customers WHERE Segment = 'SME'
actual: SELECT (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency='CZK') AS CountCZK, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency='EUR') AS CountEUR, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency='CZK')-(SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE Currency='EUR') AS Difference

question: Which LAM customer used the Euro as their currency and had the highest consumption in October 2013?
expected: SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date = '201310' AND T1.Currency = 'EUR' GROUP BY T1.CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='Euro' AND ym.Date BETWEEN 20131001 AND 20131031 GROUP BY c.CustomerID ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Who among KAM's customers consumed the most? How much did it consume?
expected: SELECT T2.CustomerID, SUM(T2.Consumption) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'KAM' GROUP BY T2.CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, SUM(ym.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers c JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID=ym.CustomerID GROUP BY c.CustomerID ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: How much did the KAM customers consume in total in May 2013?
expected: SELECT SUM(T2.Consumption) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.Date = '201305' AND T1.Segment = 'KAM'
actual: SELECT SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment='KAM' AND t.Date>='2013-05-01' AND t.Date<'2013-06-01';

question: How many percent of LAM customer consumed more than 46.73?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T2.Consumption > 46.73, 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN y.Consumption>46.73 THEN y.CustomerID END)*100.0/COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)) AS Percentage FROM yearmonth y JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Segment='LAM';

question: Which country has more "value for money" gas stations? Please give a total number of "value for money" gas stations in each country.
expected: SELECT Country , ( SELECT COUNT(GasStationID) FROM gasstations WHERE Segment = 'Value for money' ) FROM gasstations WHERE Segment = 'Value for money' GROUP BY Country ORDER BY COUNT(GasStationID) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT Country, COUNT(*) AS TotalValueForMoneyGasStations FROM gasstations WHERE Segment='value for money' GROUP BY Country ORDER BY TotalValueForMoneyGasStations DESC;

question: What percentage of KAM customers pay in euros?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(Currency = 'EUR') AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(CustomerID) FROM customers WHERE Segment = 'KAM'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN Currency='EUR' THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS Percentage_EUR_Payers FROM customers WHERE Segment='KAM';

question: In February 2012, what percentage of customers consumed more than 528.3?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(Consumption > 528.3, 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(CustomerID) FROM yearmonth WHERE Date = '201202'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN Consumption>528.3 THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS Percentage FROM yearmonth WHERE Date>=20120201 AND Date<20120301;

question: What percentage of Slovakian gas stations are premium?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(Segment = 'Premium', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(GasStationID) FROM gasstations WHERE Country = 'SVK'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN Segment='premium' THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS premium_percentage FROM gasstations WHERE Country='Slovakia';

question: Which client ID consumed the most in September 2013?

actual: SELECT CustomerID, SUM(Amount) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date>='2013-09-01' AND Date<'2013-10-01' GROUP BY CustomerID ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Which client segment consumed the least in September 2013?
expected: SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.Date = '201309' GROUP BY T1.CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT c.Segment, SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE t.Date>='2013-09-01' AND t.Date<'2013-10-01' GROUP BY c.Segment ORDER BY TotalConsumption ASC LIMIT 1;

question: Which SME customer consumed the least in June 2012?

question: What is the highest monthly consumption in the year 2012?
expected: SELECT SUM(Consumption) FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY SUBSTRING(Date, 5, 2) ORDER BY SUM(Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT MAX(MonthlyConsumption) AS HighestMonthlyConsumption FROM ( SELECT strftime('%Y-%m', Date) AS YearMonth, SUM(Consumption) AS MonthlyConsumption FROM yearmonth WHERE Date>='2012-01-01' AND Date<'2013-01-01' GROUP BY YearMonth ) AS MonthlyData;

question: What is the biggest monthly consumption of the customers who use euro as their currency?

question: Please list the product description of the products consumed in September, 2013.
expected: SELECT T3.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID INNER JOIN products AS T3 ON T1.ProductID = T3.ProductID WHERE T2.Date = '201309'

question: Please list the countries of the gas stations with transactions taken place in June, 2013.

question: Please list the chains of the gas stations with transactions in euro.

actual: SELECT DISTINCT gs.ChainID FROM gasstations gs JOIN transactions_1k t ON gs.GasStationID=t.GasStationID JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='EUR';

question: For all the transactions happened during 8:00-9:00 in 2012/8/26, how many happened in CZE?

question: There's one customer spent 214582.17 in the June of 2013, which currency did he/she use?
expected: SELECT T2.Currency FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '201306' AND T1.Consumption = 214582.17
actual: SELECT c.Currency FROM customers c JOIN transactions_1k t ON c.CustomerID=t.CustomerID WHERE t.Date>='2013-06-01' AND t.Date<'2013-07-01' AND t.Amount*t.Price=214582.17 LIMIT 1;

question: Which country was the card owner of No.667467 in?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.CardID = '667467'
actual: SELECT g.Country FROM transactions_1k t JOIN gasstations g ON t.GasStationID=g.GasStationID WHERE t.CardID=667467;

question: What's the nationality of the customer who spent 548.4 in 2012/8/24?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-24' AND T1.Price = 548.4
actual: SELECT c.Country FROM customers c JOIN transactions_1k t ON c.CustomerID=t.CustomerID JOIN gasstations g ON t.GasStationID=g.GasStationID WHERE t.Date='2012-08-24' AND t.Amount=548.4;

question: What is the percentage of the customers who used EUR in 2012/8/25?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T2.Currency = 'EUR', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25'
actual: SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT c.CustomerID)*100.0/(SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) FROM customers)) AS Percentage FROM customers c JOIN transactions_1k t ON c.CustomerID=t.CustomerID WHERE c.Currency='EUR' AND t.Date='2012-08-25';

question: For the customer who paid 634.8 in 2012/8/25, what was the consumption decrease rate from Year 2012 to 2013?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2012', Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2013', Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2012', Consumption, 0)) FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID = ( SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25' AND T1.Price = 634.8 )
actual: WITH Consumption2012 AS ( SELECT SUM(Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID=(SELECT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date='2012-08-25' AND Amount=634.8) AND Date>=20120801 AND Date<20130101 ), Consumption2013 AS ( SELECT SUM(Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID=(SELECT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date='2012-08-25' AND Amount=634.8) AND Date>=20130101 AND Date<20140101 ) SELECT (Consumption2012.TotalConsumption-Consumption2013.TotalConsumption)/Consumption2012.TotalConsumption*100 AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate FROM Consumption2012, Consumption2013;

question: Which gas station has the highest amount of revenue?
expected: SELECT GasStationID FROM transactions_1k GROUP BY GasStationID ORDER BY SUM(Price) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT gs.GasStationID, SUM(t.Amount*t.Price) AS TotalRevenue FROM transactions_1k t JOIN gasstations gs ON t.GasStationID=gs.GasStationID GROUP BY gs.GasStationID ORDER BY TotalRevenue DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the percentage of "premium" against the overall segment in "SVK"?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(Country = 'SVK' AND Segment = 'Premium', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(GasStationID) FROM gasstations
actual: SELECT (COUNT(CASE WHEN c.Segment='premium' THEN 1 END)*100.0/COUNT(*)) AS premium_percentage FROM customers c JOIN gasstations g ON c.CustomerID=g.GasStationID WHERE g.Country='SVK';

question: What is the amount spent by customer "38508" at the gas stations? How much had the customer spent in January 2012?
expected: SELECT SUM(T1.Price) , SUM(IIF(T3.Date = '201201', T1.Price, 0)) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T3 ON T1.CustomerID = T3.CustomerID WHERE T1.CustomerID = '38508'
actual: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y-%m', Date)='2012-01' THEN Amount ELSE 0 END) AS Amount_Spent_January_2012, SUM(Amount) AS Total_Amount_Spent FROM transactions_1k WHERE CustomerID=38508 AND GasStationID IN (SELECT GasStationID FROM gasstations);

question: Which are the top five best selling products? Please state the full name of them.
expected: SELECT T2.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.ProductID = T2.ProductID ORDER BY T1.Amount DESC LIMIT 5
actual: SELECT p.Description, SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalSales FROM transactions_1k t JOIN products p ON t.ProductID=p.ProductID GROUP BY p.Description ORDER BY TotalSales DESC LIMIT 5;

question: Who is the top spending customer and how much is the average price per single item purchased by this customer? What currency was being used?
expected: SELECT T2.CustomerID, SUM(T2.Price / T2.Amount), T1.Currency FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.CustomerID = ( SELECT CustomerID FROM yearmonth ORDER BY Consumption DESC LIMIT 1 ) GROUP BY T2.CustomerID, T1.Currency
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, SUM(t.Price*t.Amount) AS TotalSpending, AVG(t.Price) AS AveragePricePerItem, c.Currency FROM transactions_1k t JOIN customers c ON t.CustomerID=c.CustomerID GROUP BY c.CustomerID, c.Currency ORDER BY TotalSpending DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Which country had the gas station that sold the most expensive product id No.2 for one unit?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.ProductID = 2 ORDER BY T1.Price DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT gs.Country FROM transactions_1k t JOIN gasstations gs ON t.GasStationID=gs.GasStationID WHERE t.ProductID=2 ORDER BY t.Price DESC LIMIT 1;

question: For all the people who paid more than 29.00 per unit of product id No.5. Give their consumption status in the August of 2012.
expected: SELECT T2.CustomerID, T2.Consumption FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Price / T1.Amount > 29.00 AND T1.ProductID = 5 AND T2.Date = '201208'
actual: SELECT c.CustomerID, y.Consumption FROM customers c JOIN transactions_1k t ON c.CustomerID=t.CustomerID JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID=y.CustomerID WHERE t.ProductID=5 AND t.Price>29.00 AND y.Date=201208;
